'''Ashwath Aiyappa''' (18 November 1983 &ndash; 17 April 2014) was an Indian [[cricket]]er. He played three [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches for [[Karnataka cricket team|Karnataka]] in 2001/02.<ref name="Bio">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/26310.html |title=Ashwath Aiyappa |accessdate=13 May 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> He drowned while trying to save his brother in a reservoir.<ref name="IE">{{Cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/wicketkeeper-leaves-behind-a-book-and-lessons-of-a-sporting-life/ |title=Wicketkeeper Ashwath Aiyappa leaves behind a book, and lessons of a sporting life |accessdate=13 May 2016 |work=Indian Express}}</ref><ref name="BM">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/bangalore/others/Cricketer-drowns-trying-to-save-bro/articleshow/33919449.cms |title=Cricketer drowns trying to save bro |accessdate=13 May 2016 |work=Bangalore Mirror}}</ref>
