{{italic title}} In '''''Marais v The Master''''', an important case in the [[Law of succession in South Africa|South African law of succession]], the [[testator]], who had divorced from his wife in 1972, bequeathed his entire [[Estate (law)|estate]] to her in 1977. Before his death, he wrote words on his copy of the [[Will and testament|will]] and on a letter from his [[Lawyer|attorney]], attempting to revoke the will and direct that his mother was to be his sole heir. The court held that there had been a clear intention to revoke the will and to nominate his mother as sole beneficiary.
== See also == * [[South African law of succession]]
