{{Infobox person | name = Vlassis Bonatsos | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date |1949|11|30}} | birth_place = [[Xylokastro]], [[Greece]] | death_date = {{Death date and age |2004|10|14|1949|11|30}} | death_place = [[Athens, Greece]] | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | othername = | occupation = Actor, TV-presenter, singer | yearsactive = | spouse = Martha Koutoumanou (1996–2004) }}
'''Vlassis Bonatsos''' ({{lang-gr|Βλάσσης Μπονάτσος}}) (November 30, 1949 – October 14, 2004) was a popular [[Greece|Greek]] entertainer and singer.
== Biography == His father was a judicial officer and his mother was a piano teacher. Vlassis started his music career by creating a group named "'''PELOMA BOKIOU'''" ("ΠΕΛΟΜΑ ΜΠΟΚΙΟΥ") in the early 1970s. The band members came up with the name after combining syllables of their last names: Da'''PE'''ris, '''LO'''gothetis, '''MA'''rinakis, '''BO'''natsos and '''KIOY'''rktsoglou. In the early 1980s he costarred in the legendary theatrical play "[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]" starring [[Aliki Vougiouklaki]] (Αλίκη Βουγιουκλάκη) and him as [[Che Guevara|Che]]. He maintained a relationship with the "national" Star of Greece (Vougiouklaki was used to be called that) for several years. Then he took up acting and starred in Greek movies, but his fame reached its peak in the 1990s when he started participating in popular TV series such as "Aparadektoi" (1991). He is also remembered as a presenter of iconic TV shows and gameshows on Greek TV including the Greek version of ''[[Family Feud]]'' (named in Greek: ''Kontres''). In ''Kontres'' his memorable catchphrase was "Tora!!!!!" (Now!!!) with a characteristic sudden raise in his voice (almost yelling). He died suddenly in 2004, aged 54. According to the press his death cause was [[Asphyxia|asphyxiation]], due to [[obstructive laryngitis]].
