{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} [[Image:ÄlgenStolta.jpg|220px|thumb|Stolta pulls men in a horse-cart, c.1908. Anders Jansson at reins with Johan Blad]] [[File:Stolta award 1907.jpg|thumb|Stolta's commemorative coffee service award 1907]] '''Älgen Stolta''' (in Swedish, "Älgen" means "the moose" and "Stolta" means "proud") was a [[moose]] that became known for participating in a [[harness racing|trot racing]] event in [[Falun]], Sweden, in 1907.
== History == In the early 1900s, an elk cow (adult female) died, leaving her year-old calf behind. Different sources claim the cow was a killed by a passing train, others that it drowned, but they agree it happened near the [[Dalälven|Dalälven river]] close to [[Älvkarleby]] in [[Uppland]]. Its live female calf was taken to Johan Blad, the foreman at Älvkarleö's railway park. Blad knew a [[Lineman (technician)|lineman]] called Anders Gustav Jansson who lived in Älvkarleby and had a reputation for animal husbandry, so he asked for his help with the elk which they named Stolta.<ref name=digitaltmuseum>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltmuseum.se/things/lgen-stolta-drar-spark-med-frmannen-johan/S-UM/RR0413|title=Älgen Stolta drar spark med förmannen Johan Blad och banvakten Anders Jansson vid tömmarna, Älvkarleö, Uppland 1908|trans-title=Stolta pulls sled with the foreman Johan Leaves and lineman Anders Jansson at the reins, Älvkarleö, Upland 1908|publisher=digitaltmuseum.se|accessdate=28 July 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727203313/http://www.digitaltmuseum.se/things/lgen-stolta-drar-spark-med-frmannen-johan/S-UM/RR0413|archivedate=27 July 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=digital>{{cite web |url= http://www.digitaltmuseum.se/things/lgen-stolta-drar-gigg-med-tv-mn-i/S-UM/RR0414 |title=Älgen Stolta drar gigg med två män i Järnvägsparken, Älvkarleö, Älvkarleby socken, Uppland 1908|trans-title=The elk Stolta pulls a gig with two men in the railway park, Älvkarleö, Älvkarleby parish, Uppland 1908| publisher=digitaltmuseum.se |accessdate=28 July 2014}}</ref> Stolta was raised like a tame horse;<ref name=Swedishnewspaper>{{cite web |url=http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?depth=1&hl=en&prev=/search%3Fq%3D%2522%25C3%2584lgen%2BStolta%2522%26start%3D30%26sa%3DN%26biw%3D1280%26bih%3D536&rurl=translate.google.com&sl=sv&u=http://magasin.kb.se:8080/searchinterface/page.jsp%3Fid%3Dkb:51198%26recordNumber%3D145%26totalRecordNumber%3D483&usg=ALkJrhjSmFnnpMMDKgrMHpnsHby0BGpYVA |title=Från konungens Dalabesök|trans-title=From the King's visit to Dalarna |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=16 March 1909 |website= |publisher=Dalpilen |accessdate=8 January 2014}}</ref> doing forestry work, pulling carts and sleds with material, and also used to pull a sled carrying tourists between the railway station and the tourist hotel near the waterfall in Älvkarleby.<ref name=digitaltmuseum/><ref name=digital/>
In 1907 at a winter sports festival in Falun, Stolta won a trot race against trained trotting horses over an ice-covered lake.<ref name=digitaltmuseum/><ref name=digital/> Jansson was afterwards presented with a coffee service: a coffee pot and accompanying sugar bowl and [[Creamer (vessel)|coffee creamer]].<ref name=digitaltmuseum/><ref name=digital/> The coffee pot had an inscription that read ''Minne av Vinteridrottsfästen i Falun 1907 för körning av elg'' ("Memento of Winter Sports Festival in Falun in 1907 for driving with an elk").<ref name=digitaltmuseum/><ref name=digital/> The park where Älgen Stolta was kept closed in 1909 as the area was marked as part of the reservoir for a [[Älvkarleby Hydroelectric Power Station|hydroelectric power station]].<ref name=powerplant/> Stolta was moved to the open-air museum of [[Skansen]] on the island of [[Djurgården]] in Stockholm where it was thought she could be better cared for,<ref name=powerplant>{{cite web |url=http://affarer.cc/start/1.5868860-algen-hette-stolta |title=Älgen hette Stolta |trans-title=The elk was called Stolta |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2014 |website= |publisher=Affarer |accessdate=8 March 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140308113206/http://affarer.cc/start/1.5868860-algen-hette-stolta |archivedate=8 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and her name was changed to "Lotta."<ref name=powerplant/> After the 1907 race, a rule prohibiting the use of elks as draft animals was added.<ref name=law>{{cite web |url=http://xn--lvkarle-4wa3o.se/index.php/omgivningar |title=Älvkarleö bruk: Bilder från brukets omgivningar |trans-title=Älvkarleö mill: Photos from the mill's surroundings |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2014 |website= |publisher=Älvkarleö |accessdate=8 January 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808041757/http://xn--lvkarle-4wa3o.se/index.php/omgivningar |archivedate=8 August 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
